	<text>
		<body>
			<p>In adverting to reports from this Mission with respect to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337"
					type="subject">anti-Semitic measures</term> in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1181" type="subject"
					>German-occupied countries</term>, I have the honor to submit hereunder in summary form a description of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">measures</term> recently announced in the <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press</term> directed against the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jewish population</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1181" type="subject">occupied</term>
				<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3017382/republic-of-france.html">France</placeName>, the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2750405/kingdom-of-the-netherlands.html">Netherlands</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2802361/kingdom-of-belgium.html">Belgium</placeName> and Northern France, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3038033/alsace.html">Alsace</placeName>, the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-681">General Government</orgName> (of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>), and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovakia</placeName>. […]</p>
			<p><orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-681">General Government</orgName> (of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>): In view of the heavy <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-552" type="subject">migration</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">population</term> into the new <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>, the period for the completion of voluntary establishment
				there by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-820" type="subject">families</term> from other quarters of the city has
				been extended through <date when="1940-11-15">November 15</date>. At the same time the limits of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> have been enlarged to take in certain
				additional blocks and it is feared that this enlargement may mean the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-552" type="subject">moving into</term> the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> not as yet resident in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>. It has also been decided to force the transfer of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term> owned and operated <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-937" type="subject">industrial plants</term> into the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> and the removal from the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> of many such enterprises carried on
				therein by <term ref="#ehri_dr_gentile">non-Jews</term>. There are taking place conversations between the owners of such plants as to
				whether an exchange of ownership cannot be effected in a manner acceptable to both the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> and <term ref="#ehri_dr_gentile"
					>non-Jews</term>. The authorities express the hope that this extension of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> idea to include <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-937" type="subject">industrial enterprises</term> may be carried out
				without undue delay.</p>
			<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovakia</placeName>: A decree is reported to be under
				preparation by the <orgName ref="#ehri_dr_government_slovakian">Slovakian Government</orgName> which will block <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-931" type="subject"> accounts in banking</term> establishments and will
				make obligatory the deposit of all securities belonging to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864"
					type="subject">Jewish</term> persons or <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-922">enterprises</term>.
				Payments to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> will only be possible
				through such <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-931" type="subject">blocked accounts</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> will only be allowed to withdraw up to a
				maximum of 5,000 crowns per week on the basis of a special and individual permit from their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-931" type="subject">blocked accounts</term>.</p>
			<p>The above developments indicate that <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">anti-Semitic measures</term> are rapidly being put
				into effect in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1181" type="subject">occupied territories</term>. At
				the same time the <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1068" type="subject">press</term> publishes articles reporting somewhat
				similar <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">measures</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Rumania</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/7500737/federal-republic-of-yugoslavia.html">Jugoslavia</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/732800/republic-of-bulgaria.html">Bulgaria</placeName> and <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_countries_vichy_france">unoccupied France</term>. There appears, consequently, to be a definite program of carrying
					<term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-329" type="subject">anti-Semitism</term> beyond the <term
					ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_germans">German</term> borders into such countries as come into the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1028" type="subject">German sphere of influence</term>.</p>
